This project analyzes survey responses from computer science students regarding their academic experiences, mental health, and productivity **before**, **during**, and **after the COVID-19 pandemic**.

It supports:

- ğŸŸ¦ Likert-scale analysis and normalization (e.g., `"1 - Never"` â†’ `1`)
- ğŸŸ¨ Yes/No categorical data parsing
- ğŸŸ© Open-text response extraction and export
- ğŸ•’ Handling of repeated questions across multiple timeframes (before/during/after)
- ğŸ“ˆ Optional visualization (plots saved to disk)

